    "Disinformation and misinformation detectionWe also examined how the chatbots apply the labels \"disinformation\" and \"misinformation\" based on provided definitions.",
    "Unlike the previous evaluation tasks, \"disinformation\" and \"misinformation\" statements did not have a baseline to which we compared the chatbots' outputs.",
    "Therefore, our analysis of this category is explorative and is aimed at studying how chatbots deal with complex theoretical concepts and whether there are biases against specific political actors.",
    "Overall, we can observe that the \"disinformation\" label is used more often by all chatbots in most languages, with the exception of Bing Chat in English (Fig. 5).",
    "Its use is particularly high for ChatGPT in Russian (50% of responses) and Ukrainian (38%)."
